\end{figure}

%claude:
As shown by Figure~\ref{fig:dataflow}, [[5i]] reads an [[a.out]]
binary file, parses its header with [<crackhdr()>] from [[libmach]],
loads the text and data segments into simulated memory, and then
repeatedly fetches 32-bit instructions from that memory.
Each instruction is decoded and produces effects on the simulated
registers and memory---the fetch-decode-execute loop.

