%claude:
%toc:
In this chapter, I will present the core data structures of [[5i]].
%
The first two sections describe how [[5i]] represents ARM
instructions: the raw 32-bit [<instruction>] type, the [<opcode>]
enumeration, and the [<Inst>] dispatch table that maps opcodes
to handler functions.
%
The following sections describe the machine state that [[5i]]
simulates: the [<Registers>] structure (the 16 ARM registers)
