\subsection{Misc instructions}

%claude:
The remaining data-processing cases are less common.
[[CMN]] (compare negative) is like [[CMP]] but adds
instead of subtracting.
[[RSB]] (reverse subtract) computes [[o2 - o1]] instead
of [[o1 - o2]], useful when the immediate is the value
you want to subtract from.
[[ADC]], [[SBC]], and [[RSC]] (add/subtract with carry)
are left unimplemented---the \plan compiler [[5c]] never
generates them.
Finally, [[MOV]] and [[MVN]] (move / move negated) set a
register to a value or its bitwise complement; despite
their names, they live in the arithmetic opcode space
rather than in load/store.

